WEBVTT

00:02.089 --> 00:04.409
So I went out with a drug dealer on...

00:04.411 --> 00:07.323
Jared S., make a better choice!

00:08.253 --> 00:09.253
Saturday night.

00:09.614 --> 00:12.940
It was incredible.
- Oh, that is so awesome.

00:12.942 --> 00:16.102
Okay, Alfred G., three, two...

00:17.453 --> 00:18.852
Not today, my friend.

00:19.555 --> 00:21.811
Was he, like, a mobster or something?

00:21.836 --> 00:25.131
No, he, like, sells Vicodin
on the low, full time.

00:25.156 --> 00:28.453
Stop. Down. Now.

00:29.219 --> 00:30.383
If you tell me he has a goatee,

00:30.385 --> 00:31.570
I'm gonna be so jealous.

00:31.773 --> 00:33.483
He was really tender.

00:33.508 --> 00:35.662
Xavier L., is that your...

00:35.664 --> 00:39.178
thank you for making a
good choice, Xavier L.

00:40.396 --> 00:42.701
But not too tender,

00:42.703 --> 00:43.579
if you know what I mean.

00:43.604 --> 00:44.681
[chuckles]

00:44.683 --> 00:47.743
Did you do the deed?
- [chuckles]

00:47.745 --> 00:50.328
Okay, Room 301, we're done down here.

00:50.353 --> 00:52.767
We do not make gestures like that.

00:53.822 --> 00:55.417
These are bad kids.

00:55.419 --> 00:56.589
The worst.

00:56.591 --> 00:59.285
[rock music]

01:02.692 --> 01:06.085
♪ Tear it down ♪
- ♪ Tear it down ♪

01:06.087 --> 01:07.502
[rock music]

01:07.527 --> 01:08.659
♪ Cake, cake, cake ♪

01:08.661 --> 01:10.628
♪ Haters gonna hate,
bakers gonna bake ♪

01:10.630 --> 01:12.730
♪ Cake in the morning ♪

01:12.732 --> 01:13.798
What's up with this cake?

01:13.800 --> 01:15.533
My class made it for
Hunger Action Month.

01:15.535 --> 01:17.268
Then shouldn't they be eating it?

01:17.270 --> 01:18.436
No. I took it away from them,

01:18.438 --> 01:20.237
so they could know the
true meaning of hunger.

01:20.239 --> 01:21.672
Well, I've decided to treat myself

01:21.674 --> 01:23.607
ever since my breakup with Jacob.

01:23.609 --> 01:24.862
How are you doing?

01:24.864 --> 01:25.843
Not that well.

01:25.845 --> 01:28.746
Hasn't it been, like, a year?

01:28.748 --> 01:30.396
14 months.

01:31.997 --> 01:35.319
Ladies, I'm so glad you're
all here for the meeting.

01:35.321 --> 01:39.557
What meeting?
- The anti-bullying committee meeting.

01:39.559 --> 01:40.891
Ms. Feldman?

01:40.893 --> 01:44.298
Ms. Feldman, are you
here for the meeting?

01:44.831 --> 01:45.915
The meeting?

01:47.017 --> 01:48.732
Yes. Yes, I am.

01:48.734 --> 01:50.367
Were you just sleeping?

01:50.369 --> 01:52.736
No. No, I was not.

01:52.738 --> 01:53.771
Okay.

01:55.395 --> 01:58.174
I just got off the phone
with Mrs. Lark from district.

01:58.176 --> 02:00.811
A while back, they
mandated that every school

02:00.813 --> 02:02.713
launch an anti-bullying program.

02:02.715 --> 02:05.316
I need this committee
to come up with ways

02:05.318 --> 02:07.284
to prevent bullying here at Fillmore.

02:07.286 --> 02:09.333
But we don't have a bullying problem.

02:09.335 --> 02:12.690
I know, but someone reported
that we didn't have a program,

02:12.692 --> 02:14.492
and now we have to have one.

02:14.494 --> 02:16.726
That was me.
- Why would you do that?

02:16.728 --> 02:18.796
But then how are we going to
know who the popular kids are?

02:18.798 --> 02:20.531
What?
- I thought I was excused

02:20.533 --> 02:22.466
from all extracurricular activities

02:22.468 --> 02:23.868
due to emotional stress.

02:23.870 --> 02:25.065
That was never a thing.

02:25.067 --> 02:27.238
This is going to make a real difference.

02:27.240 --> 02:29.507
I know in high school
when Lauren Zellnek

02:29.509 --> 02:30.808
convinced everyone that I was gay

02:30.810 --> 02:33.477
and put fetal pigs in my locker,

02:33.479 --> 02:35.565
I could have used a program like this.

02:37.831 --> 02:41.218
Anyway, I need you all to
come up with different ways

02:41.220 --> 02:43.118
to prevent bullying at Fillmore.

02:43.120 --> 02:44.955
Are you all in?
- Yes.

02:48.460 --> 02:51.262
Because with cutbacks
looming, it's volunteering

02:51.264 --> 02:52.630
for a program like
this that would keep you

02:52.632 --> 02:54.465
from getting fired.

02:54.467 --> 02:55.533
I'm in.
- Me, too.

02:55.535 --> 02:56.826
Yeah, I'll do it.
- Yeah, yeah.

02:56.828 --> 02:58.435
Good.
- Yay.

02:58.437 --> 03:01.360
Okay, everyone. Quiet coyote.

03:02.909 --> 03:04.375
Thank you.

03:04.377 --> 03:07.545
Now today I want to talk
to you guys about bullies.

03:07.547 --> 03:09.346
Did you know that the word "bully"

03:09.348 --> 03:10.830
originally meant "sweetheart"?

03:12.244 --> 03:13.684
Makes a lot of sense
when you think about it.

03:13.686 --> 03:17.938
Because sometimes a bully
starts out as a sweetheart.

03:18.080 --> 03:19.619
That's how they get you.

03:20.393 --> 03:23.527
A bully is someone who generally
disregards your feelings,

03:23.529 --> 03:24.528
ignores your texts,

03:24.530 --> 03:26.463
and changes the password on
your joint Netflix account

03:26.465 --> 03:28.766
two days after you break up.
- Uh, Ms. Watson...

03:28.768 --> 03:31.468
A bully can also take you
to Nashville one weekend

03:31.470 --> 03:32.770
on his frequent flier miles,

03:32.772 --> 03:33.737
treat you to bottomless mimosas,

03:33.739 --> 03:35.973
and then on Monday tell you it's over.

03:35.975 --> 03:37.310
What's a mimosa?

03:37.312 --> 03:39.513
It's something women in their 20s order

03:39.538 --> 03:41.612
so they can feel better
about drinking in the morning.

03:41.614 --> 03:44.337
<i>I thought we were going
to read Cinderella today.</i>

03:44.339 --> 03:45.363
No.

03:45.957 --> 03:48.283
No, I'm not going to be
reading you any fairy tales

03:48.285 --> 03:49.687
because they're lies.

03:49.689 --> 03:52.957
The truth is, kids,
sometimes Prince Charming

03:52.959 --> 03:54.729
wants to date other people, you know?

03:54.971 --> 03:57.625
And just because you leave
a shoe in his apartment

03:57.627 --> 04:00.431
doesn't mean you can
show up whenever you want.

04:00.433 --> 04:04.244
Nobody lives happily
ever after. Trust me.

04:04.246 --> 04:06.804
My cousin Connie's 39.
She just got divorced,

04:06.806 --> 04:08.973
and now she works part-time at a Chicos.

04:08.975 --> 04:11.442
Chicos?
- Yeah, Chicos.

04:11.444 --> 04:13.838
It's Spanish for big shoulders.

04:13.840 --> 04:20.039
[rock music]

04:20.041 --> 04:22.886
Ms. Snap, I drew you a picture of us.

04:22.888 --> 04:24.641
Thank you so much.

04:28.928 --> 04:30.884
Is that supposed to be me?

04:30.886 --> 04:32.796
Yeah.

04:32.798 --> 04:34.148
Where are my cheekbones?

04:36.586 --> 04:38.002
Uh...
- Couple of tips.

04:38.004 --> 04:39.576
We have the same size wrists,

04:39.578 --> 04:41.750
so why do you draw me
with the bigger body?

04:42.055 --> 04:43.959
I'm not Miley Cyrus. I
don't have horse teeth.

04:44.662 --> 04:46.364
Okay.
- This is really bad.

04:46.366 --> 04:47.211
It's disgusting.

04:47.213 --> 04:49.287
Let's just consider this a rough draft.

04:51.608 --> 04:53.542
Debbie?

04:53.544 --> 04:54.857
Love that chambray dress.

04:56.357 --> 04:58.956
What if we had them write down
what they did wrong on signs

04:58.958 --> 05:00.699
and then they could wear
them around their necks

05:00.724 --> 05:02.237
like that dog-shaming website?

05:02.239 --> 05:03.427
They're not dogs.

05:03.429 --> 05:05.763
Sometimes bullying can be a good thing.

05:05.765 --> 05:08.065
In high school, my best friend Randy

05:08.067 --> 05:09.800
got called the f-word every day

05:09.802 --> 05:11.769
and now he's head pastor of his church.

05:11.771 --> 05:14.972
Lauren Zellnek tortured
me in high school.

05:14.974 --> 05:17.569
It got so bad that I got hemorrhoids

05:17.571 --> 05:20.678
and I had to sit on an
innertube in all of my classes.

05:20.680 --> 05:23.770
You must have felt like you
were at the pool all day.

05:24.583 --> 05:26.950
Sorry. The hot dad
dropped his son off late

05:26.952 --> 05:29.213
and I had to flirt with him.

05:29.215 --> 05:30.434
He is so hot.

05:30.459 --> 05:32.313
Did you bring any ideas?
- Yes, I did.

05:33.959 --> 05:36.060
A compliments board is a great idea.

05:36.062 --> 05:37.628
I think we should christen it by giving

05:37.630 --> 05:38.719
each other compliments.

05:40.431 --> 05:41.890
Um, I'll start.

05:42.447 --> 05:46.070
Chelsea, I think your hair
looks really nice today.

05:46.072 --> 05:48.672
I look like a piece of [bleep].

05:48.674 --> 05:51.402
So should I not write that down or...

05:52.044 --> 05:54.478
Caroline, um...

05:54.480 --> 05:57.003
I really like how you
handled your breakup.

05:57.883 --> 05:59.175
That's not a compliment.

06:00.464 --> 06:02.720
For someone who doesn't
have a lot going on for them,

06:02.722 --> 06:05.055
you have a lot of confidence.

06:05.057 --> 06:06.480
Thank you so much.

06:12.865 --> 06:15.579
Raise your hand if you've
ever bullied someone.

06:17.563 --> 06:21.071
Okay, guys, bullying
is not just pushing,

06:21.073 --> 06:22.606
beating, and shoving.

06:22.608 --> 06:24.908
We can also hurt each
other with our words.

06:24.910 --> 06:28.011
So why don't we go ahead
and shout out some examples

06:28.013 --> 06:29.122
of verbal bullying?

06:29.239 --> 06:30.614
Marty has a butt chin.

06:30.616 --> 06:33.150
Yes. That is bullying.

06:33.152 --> 06:33.917
Any other examples?

06:33.919 --> 06:36.190
Denise doesn't know who her dad is.

06:36.192 --> 06:38.895
Mm, this is an interesting example.

06:38.920 --> 06:41.981
It sounds like bullying, but
is also a factual statement.

06:41.983 --> 06:43.293
So is it bullying?

06:43.295 --> 06:45.129
I don't know the answer there.

06:45.131 --> 06:47.949
Ms. Feldman's gonna be
honest with you guys.

06:48.316 --> 06:49.340
I don't know.

06:50.270 --> 06:51.637
This is one of those times

06:51.662 --> 06:52.870
where we're all on the
same page learning together,

06:52.872 --> 06:54.738
and it's really fun.

06:54.740 --> 06:57.480
Maggie has the same
haircut as my Aunt Linda.

06:57.482 --> 06:59.109
My mom made me get this haircut.

06:59.111 --> 07:01.712
Alison's mom is fat. Chuck's mom is fat.

07:01.714 --> 07:03.580
Brendan's mom is fat.

07:03.582 --> 07:04.915
Alison, Chuck, and Brendan's dads

07:04.917 --> 07:06.784
like it like that.

07:06.786 --> 07:07.885
A lot of guys do.

07:07.887 --> 07:09.653
Did someone already do Maggie's haircut?

07:09.655 --> 07:12.956
You guys, my mom made me go
to her hairdresser, Doris.

07:12.958 --> 07:14.191
And Doris only knows one haircut.

07:14.193 --> 07:18.162
I don't think Maggie's
haircut is a problem, you guys.

07:18.164 --> 07:19.569
I think it's Doris.

07:19.571 --> 07:22.166
But if we all agree that
Maggie's haircut is bad,

07:22.168 --> 07:23.491
then is that bullying?

07:23.493 --> 07:25.102
Yeah. I think it is.

07:25.104 --> 07:27.704
It's 'cause people are very dark inside.

07:27.706 --> 07:30.385
People are very sad and dark inside.

07:32.338 --> 07:33.710
Okay, a little too much?

07:33.712 --> 07:36.180
We'll save that for after lunch.

07:36.182 --> 07:42.853
[kids sobbing]

07:44.190 --> 07:46.223
Oh, my God. What happened?

07:46.225 --> 07:47.925
<i>- This is horrible.
- _</i>

07:47.927 --> 07:49.959
I didn't want this haircut.

07:49.961 --> 07:51.755
Oh, Maggie, honey, ignore the board.

07:51.757 --> 07:52.974
You're beautiful.

07:52.976 --> 07:54.097
Where did they come
up with these insults?

07:54.099 --> 07:56.300
<i>This is the opposite of compliments.</i>

07:56.302 --> 07:57.334
This is bullying.

07:57.336 --> 07:59.863
Which is progress because this morning

07:59.864 --> 08:01.979
they didn't even know you
could bully with words?

08:02.279 --> 08:04.092
Unbelievable.

08:05.110 --> 08:08.512
[rock music]

08:12.200 --> 08:16.503
The compliments board was a disaster.

08:21.066 --> 08:24.183
Now does anyone have any
ideas that are actually good?

08:24.208 --> 08:25.925
We really need an anti-bullying club.

08:25.927 --> 08:27.736
What if we implement a buddy system

08:27.738 --> 08:29.705
where you always have one
friend you can really count on?

08:29.707 --> 08:31.158
What if they don't even have one friend?

08:31.160 --> 08:33.212
What if we made sure kids
only said nice things?

08:33.238 --> 08:34.956
We can't restrict their free speech.

08:34.981 --> 08:37.251
I really think we need
an anti-bullying club.

08:37.253 --> 08:38.501
Now that is a good idea.

08:38.503 --> 08:39.587
I love that.
- Yeah. Yeah.

08:39.589 --> 08:40.809
I just suggested that.

08:40.812 --> 08:41.878
What would they do in the club?

08:41.880 --> 08:42.879
It would be a safe place

08:42.881 --> 08:44.096
for them to talk about their feelings.

08:44.097 --> 08:45.448
They could make potato batteries.

08:45.450 --> 08:46.582
They could check their email.

08:46.584 --> 08:47.717
It could just be a safe place

08:47.719 --> 08:48.926
for them to talk about their feelings.

08:48.928 --> 08:49.863
That's it. Perfect.

08:49.865 --> 08:51.454
Did I not just say that?

08:51.456 --> 08:52.855
We'd need someone to be in charge.

08:52.857 --> 08:54.079
I'm happy to offer my classroom.

08:54.081 --> 08:56.585
I used to cut myself.

08:56.587 --> 09:01.083
This is my pain.

09:01.085 --> 09:03.866
I'm gonna run this club.

09:03.868 --> 09:06.725
I am.

09:06.750 --> 09:08.874
This is a safe place.

09:08.899 --> 09:10.752
I want you all to feel
that you can come here

09:10.754 --> 09:12.087
and talk about issues and troubles

09:12.089 --> 09:13.989
you're having here at school, okay?

09:13.991 --> 09:17.292
Does anyone want to share anything?

09:17.294 --> 09:18.593
Brad says I smell like Funyons.

09:18.595 --> 09:20.929
People love Funyons. They're fun.

09:20.931 --> 09:25.834
Listen, in high school,
Lauren Zellnek changed my name

09:25.836 --> 09:28.103
from Deb Adler to Dumb Fatter,

09:28.105 --> 09:30.670
which made me develop
an eating disorder.

09:30.672 --> 09:32.899
Has anyone had any
experiences like that?

09:33.860 --> 09:35.443
No? Really?

09:35.445 --> 09:38.888
No one's ever sprayed you
in the face with Windex?

09:39.466 --> 09:40.840
No one's ever started a
rumor that you were gay

09:40.865 --> 09:43.956
<i>because you won tickets to
The Rosie O'Donnell Show?</i>

09:43.958 --> 09:47.350
Did Lauren Zellnek make you
take a shot from a diva cup?

09:47.351 --> 09:49.423
Jesus Christ.

09:49.487 --> 09:52.994
